ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY

Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: What number best describes how you have felt overall since you began taking this medication?
Notes: 1 = Very much better; 2 = Much better; 3 = A little better; 4 = No change; 5 = A little worse; 6 = Much worse; 7 = Very much worse

ElementDescription: Check the one number that best describes how your symptoms are now
Please choose the response below that best describes the overall severity of your mental health symptoms over the past 7 days.
Notes: 1= No symptoms/normal; 2= Mild; 3= Moderate; 4= Severe; 5= Very Severe

ElementDescription: Patient Global Impression since last visit or last 6 months:  Disease Status
Patient Global Impression since last visit or last 6 months:  Walking Status
Patient Global Impression since last visit or last 6 months:  Hand Function Status
Patient Global Impression since last visit or last 6 months:  Speech Status

Notes: e.g., Baseline, 6-Month Follow Up, Year 2; Morning, At Bedtime

ElementDescription: Since the start of the study (treatment), my overall pain is
Notes: 0= Very much improved; 1= Much improved; 2= Minimally improved; 3= No change; 4= Minimally worse; 5= Much worse; 6= Very much worse
